					<p>[&#8230;] often talks about how retailers including Target were victimized by malware on their point-of-sale (PoS) systems, and how credit card processing in the U.S. &#8212; which still relies on old-fashioned [&#8230;]</p>
					<a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='https://news.sophos.com/en-us/2014/01/24/target-neiman-marcus-card-data-thefts-ram-scraper-malware-and-you/?replytocom=444#respond' data-commentid="444" data-postid="23925" data-belowelement="comment-444" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Sophos at BSides Austin: Credit card security and PCI DSS compliance, post-Target | Sophos Blog" aria-label='Reply to Sophos at BSides Austin: Credit card security and PCI DSS compliance, post-Target | Sophos Blog'>Reply</a>				</div>
			</div>

	</article>
